Certainly! Here's a simple C code snippet to determine if a given number is even or odd:

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int number;

    // Ask the user to enter a number
    printf("Enter an integer: ");
    scanf("%d", &number);

    // Determine if the number is even or odd
    if (number % 2 == 0) {
        printf("%d is even.\n", number);
    } else {
        printf("%d is odd.\n", number);
    }

    return 0;
}
```

This program prompts the user to enter an integer, then it checks if the number is divisible by 2 using the modulus operator `%`. If the remainder is 0, the number is even; otherwise, it's odd.
